						               													<description>Micro Baseball is a micro version of the game of baseball using dice, tokens and 9-cards.  As the pitcher you decide your pitch with one of six pitch cards.  As the batter you pick your batting style card but hide it from the opponent.  You roll four colored dice to prepare for the pitch and then determine the amount of dice to adjust your swing and for power based on your batting style.  You can then roll dice to adjust the swing to match the pitch.  If you match you get a HIT and then determine how much power you put into the swing.  The power determines how far into the field the ball travels.  When there is a HIT, the opponent must place his player&amp;rsquo;s &amp;ldquo;up to 5 dice&amp;rdquo; on the field in zones to see if they make the out. &amp;#10;You can play a full game solo against an A.I. Bot or 2-player.  All the same rules apply to actual game of baseball with pitching, hitting and fielding but I removed balls and strikes to speed up play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
